text: Anicka Newell (born August 5, 1993 in Denton, Texas) is a Canadian track and field athlete competing in the pole vault.COC ProifleIAAF Profile ==Professional== Newell placed 1st at 2018 Canadian Athletics Championships in Ottawa & cleared to qualify for August 11 2018 NACAC Championships in Torontobut she did not clear a height (NH). Newell placed 7th in Athletics at the 2018 Commonwealth Games – Women's pole vault cleared . Anicka Newell placed 12th in women's pole vault at 2017 World Championship cleared on the second attempt. Newell cleared at Texas State University San Marcos in June 2017 which is the second highest athlete all-time in Athletics Canada behind Alysha Newman.Athletics Canada Pole Vault Rankings In July 2016, she was officially named to Canada's Olympic team. Newell placed 29th at Athletics at the 2016 Summer Olympics – Women's pole vault cleared .
